card.desc:
Created issue.
MICROSOFT_CASB currently using FILE_ event types which don't make sense b/c it's a remote access / zero trust type solution. These events typically don't have hashes and IP addresses would not be asset ips (they're ISP carrier peering IPs or in the best case private connectivity nat gateway ips).

go/udm:cloudy has event types for interacting with cloud resources in addition to USER_LOGIN which will likely be a much better fit than the existing ones.

Can leverage existing sample logs in code search for this enhancement, user specific data sets not required.

Related issue: b/159167920
Similar issue: b/160260894
